The paper discusses the use of a 1D Convolutional Neural Network (1DCNN) to classify EEG and EOG data for the identification of ischemic stroke. This involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the study involves the analysis of biological data related to stroke, which could also place it in the cs.BIO (Bioinformatics) sub-category. The use of EEG and EOG data also suggests a potential application in the field of human-computer interaction, which could place it in the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. Finally, the study involves the use of Batch Normalization to accelerate the training process, which could also place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
